)

sec.p:
During the fieldwork, the Spanish methodologies consider the disposal place where the waste can be found including the criteria to determine cleanliness indexes. The created methodology also considers these factors, and additionally, indicators for each waste category (CL
i
) were developed as well as for each disposal place (CL
x
), besides the indicator for the street cleanliness level itself (CL). Instead, AVPU’s methodology does not consider the waste disposal place to calculate the cleanliness level. The present methodology aims to support actions of improvement in the services; thus, the place and specific type of waste is highly relevant to promote target measures of improvement.
